r workspace/head-info API that supports both GitButler\n  and plain Git modes. Do not add an agentlog-specific plain-Git model unless\n  the shared API proves insufficient.\n- Do not store separate checked-out references or graph entrypoint markers in\n  the turn snapshot.\n- Association scoring is automatic, read-time, explainable, and conservative.\n  Tune exact thresholds after impleme\n[TRUNCATED]\nceive the set of\nnewly accepted records and write a corresponding turn object.\n\n`but-agentlog` should probably become a higher-level GitButler crate for this\nfeature and depend on other `but-*` crates instead of reimplementing workspace\ninspection. The likely shape is:\n\n- depend on `but-ctx` so capture can build the same repository/workspace context\n  as the rest of GitButler\n- prefer reusable `but-api` entry points when they already provide the product\n  shape we need\n- use `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree` or\n  `but_api::diff::changes_in_worktree_with_perm` for uncommitted worktree files\n- use the same underlying workspace model as `but_api::legacy::workspace::head_info`\n  for stack/branch snapshots, but do not use an API shape that prunes the view\n  to the graph entrypoint; if needed, add an unpruned `but-api` entry point or\n  call `but_workspace::head_info` from an agentlog-local snapshot adapter\n\nThis means the first implementation can capture environment snapshots from the\nsame workspace and diff APIs the app already trusts. If this dependency shape\nbecomes too costly later, it can be replaced behind an agentlog-local snapshot\nadapter without changing the stored turn model.\n\nOne possible storage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n```\n\n`TurnSummary` is cheap to scan for session timelines and handoff windows. It\nshould not duplicate branch, review, change, file, or environment evidence from\nthe detail. A useful v1 shape is:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"captured_at\": \"2026-05-20T18:42:11.123Z\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-9988776655443322\",\n  \"record_count\": 3,\n  \"first_record_index\": 42,\n  \"last_record_index\": 44,\n  \"previous_turn_key\": \"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\n  \"environment_snapshot_status\": \"complete\"\n}\n```\n\nThe summary lives under a session key, so it does not need to repeat\n`session_key`. `source_key` and the record index bounds are convenience fields\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:10:53.000Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}